    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou1-cpb-hemolysis-claim",
    "type": "Claim",
    "name": "CFD model adequately predicts worst-case hemolysis for Class II CPB device at MRL 2",
    "description": "The CFD hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump has been assessed as credible for identifying worst-case operating conditions across the five designated flow-speed combinations under CPB conditions. The relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by the model remains below the acceptance threshold of 1.0 at all evaluated operating points, and the model's sensitivity to geometric tolerances is sufficient to support the intended regulatory decision. This claim is supported by the full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment conducted at Model Risk Level 2.",
    "claimScope": "Class II CPB device; 5 operating points (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM); RH < 1 acceptance criterion; geometric tolerance sensitivity analysis",
    "claimPurpose": "Provide regulatory evidence that CFD-predicted hemolysis is adequate for worst-case identification without exhaustive physical testing"
  },
